President Muhammadu Buhari has extended his condolences over the passing of the former Military Governor of North Central State, Brigadier-General Abba Kyari, (rtd). According to a statement by his senior special assistant media, Garba Shehu,In a message to the the government and people of Kaduna, Katsina and Borno states on Sunday evening, President Buhari said “we are extremely saddened by the news of General Abba Kyari’s passing away, an officer and a gentleman for whom we have a lot respect.” He prayed to Allah to accept his soul, and grant fortitude to the family and friends he left behind to bear the loss.